<div class="main-features">

	<div class="feature made-for-app">
		<h2>Super performance</h2>

		<p>
			Onsen UI is designed and implemented to deliver unprecedented user experience for your apps. If you are stuck in getting native-level performance, try Onsen UI and you'll feel the difference right away.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="feature custom-elements-based">
		<h2>Multi-screen support with wider device support range, including tablets and Android 2.3</h2>

		<p>
			Onsen UI is responsive. It adjusts the view based on the screen sizes. For example, use ons-split-view tag to have two-column view for tablets and one-column view for smartphones.

Onsen UI also have wider support range for devices. It is fully tested and works well with Android 2.3 and up, iOS 6 and up, Firefox OS, Chrome, and Safari.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="feature built-with">
		<h2>Develop native-like PhoneGap / Cordova apps and mobile websites</h2>

		<p>
			Onsen UI is a perfect solution for developing hybrid apps. That's because our priority is performance and ease of use. Another option is to deploy your apps to the server and make it as a tool to build a performance website. 
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="feature beautiful-and-smooth">
		<h2>Simple to use</h2>

		<p>
			Onsen UI is inspired by Web Components. All the UI components are tags. So, if you want to place a button in a page, you'll add an <ons-button>. It's just that easy.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="feature beautiful-and-smooth">
		<h2>Works well with jQuery and AngularJS</h2>

		<p>
